Health workers wearing PPE prepare to test a woman for COVID-19. AFP/Emmanuel Croset JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 16,585 COVID-19 new cases in the last 24 hours. That brings the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 2 062,896. READ: COVID-19 | Gauteng remains epicentre - Health Dept A total of 54,879 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours which represents a 30.2% positivity rate. A further 333 COVID-19 related deaths have been reported, bringing total fatalities to 61,840 to date. The cumulative number of #COVID19 cases reported in South Africa is 2 062 896 with 16 585 new cases reported today. The number of new deaths reported is 333 and total number of deaths is 61 840. The number of recoveries is 1 808 082 with a recovery rate of 87.6% #CoronaVirusSA pic.twitter.com/Hdi2ze9K1o